# DTO Conventions

- DTOs are plain property bags for API contracts — no constructors, static factories, or mapping methods on the DTO class itself.
- Do not set default values on DTO properties; defaults belong on entities or are supplied by callers/mappers at mapping time.

```csharp
// ❌ BAD
public class StockDto
{
    public string Currency { get; set; } = "USD";
    public static StockDto FromEntity(Stock stock) => new() { ... };
}

// ✅ GOOD
public class StockDto
{
    public string Currency { get; set; }
}
```
